{"title":"Mark Lutter reports on the Bahamas (from my email)","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/899032574/0/marginalrevolution~Mark-Lutter-reports-on-the-Bahamas-from-my-email.html","date":1717688005000,"content":"<p>I won’t double indent, this is all Mark:</p>\r\n<p>“The Prime Minister of the Bahamas recently gave a <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://secure-web.cisco.com/1HGRCe6h2zOIxhh21v9aAE4PvmPSHHWdN2wbZDcLuCm6_A0yeBjNv7s2XqUdKAiYQGXljohRRP45zQFXWR6NCdlV24g30P7v6NI-1pug2AwMG_CnJq6QKLVg0qGIYqYk4umEHurmK_PiNdJHe-MFFfVpoFqop-mc0cLJBgrWRmM3hvfb7rpShchHkBeePXwzl-NI6GgeWT6qM_9rhPo_G7K27CwfC0EmXEnSfGOvsh8wqDPgU-cOjw3PGg5ajl9oWZGhmq0fVRWfWz8uGwNe6cEZk0NFqbOZKSC2vpHQ44BYuZKDupFtrHHY3rywNi4TMo9gfCZfJyvp4QE9h6bL12hVMoT-mWDkbjq5eZoIYczP7mmsDWsxFX3UmQLAUyiGfv69Lb6lnkWOgckN44cW-HN0KdV4f0l_-zHjzRH7LeUg/https%3A%2F%2Fopm.gov.bs%2Fprime-minister-davis-grand-bahama-chamber-commerce-gbpa%2F\" target=\"_blank\">speech</a> on revitalizing Grand Bahama. He called out the current asset owners of Intercontinental Diversified Corporation, a holding company for Freeport, for not re-investing and for selling off various pieces of the asset. He wants a world class partner to develop Grand Bahama. Half his cabinet attended the speech in person. It is the strongest stance a Prime Minister has taken in 50 years with respect to Grand Bahama.</p>\r\n<p>Here is some additional background reading on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~secure-web.cisco.com/1zcDG7lBXkax5w9KMO4TayL68jhJQjVDMvdDXEIm3RJwJ4C7buwQ_B1tq1FtGd9qPz2YrrB34ClJAiUihw5FsWjUGDyH7Dpp5r3e-Ac5mn4W8WRm9JcqwRxU25agoFet9WY7kexIRG3ddKU0ryGrqY7UtLvsGU-1DIj_5G1rtOVKis3OdQh0-dyLxwQVqjXkcM2IKQUZOs0tM4zNhxxzgH0NoccQcdpFOG2F1RQy54JFD2h2n7a5wZ9zc1D8xuu7bEmjnD-7Zmjt4vzV8kZV7vbkY4IT0SrpqXNBZ5kv_rcPeWZjg44pr103b7o2k0zobFLALWUgwQTc09tAB8SaOnZWBJegb6EUbinx9mOx0MrwWOB9jAyJux_Ooh-Z3dUApMbuCw0jTUmaXizU6vT7FiGXdEeadJznJgrFdcV5jZbE/http%3A%2F%2Fjabezcorner.com%2FGrand_Bahama%2FHistory.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Grand Bahama</a> and <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://secure-web.cisco.com/1yYbuKoHUs-DAvM6reXMs-fSTftgRBjEEAN4c8p0nae4cYbGAXnQo7ASRd9IQDqYxZb5crdp7srjDwl33nEPkUSk51M_iQxPs9rvu1hrqmQGMTZuHQrGbGMytm8mEwkw5dMmsTo6uN_hNisVCiMJvCZOs_FY7LCB_ZFBbN5fpSwZeF9L8NJtDy5liop1BOvqpiHtGbWsGi0DeYKIrE97tlRinKL1We4MUNZh2lGImc1wMlOJHjfX0x_ydi5F5nTD3XKXYBZ-K1qUUrbs5Hv9L4xSIfwn4sPG9NhjHoDn_RuQiWGtea78Epk9e9VC44NbGLD-JuFmlWFKokTv196OQ09l2DbpKPm-DIO_f1fOG7LHqvlpdFGQSPJQ12liiBgV3cMuYF1UhkKgoyV9p-ud-wk2XrulvB5suCcNX76spmgc/https%3A%2F%2Fgbchamber.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F05%2FVision-2015.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Freeport</a>. The Prime Minister has two years left in his term and has made revitalizing growth on Grand Bahama his political legacy. Some key facts about Freeport</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>70k+ acres of developable land under Grand Bahama Development Company</li>\r\n<li>Infrastructure to support 250k residents, current population is 50k</li>\r\n<li>25 minute flight to Miami</li>\r\n<li>Existing legal framework for a charter city, though some of the rights of the Grand Bahama Port Authority, the city government, have been eroded over time</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>I hope you find this interesting enough to blog about and would appreciate a shout out. Happy to answer any additional questions you might have.”</p>\r\n<p><strong>TC again</strong>: Here <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://x.com/marklutter/status/1796595743991750670?s=46\" target=\"_blank\">Mark comments on Twitter</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/06/mark-lutter-reports-on-the-bahamas-from-my-email.html\">Mark Lutter reports on the Bahamas (from my email)</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<